explanation: The solution uses two pointers, one for each string. It iterates through the strings, comparing characters. If a match is found, the pointer for the subsequence string is advanced. If the subsequence string is fully traversed, it indicates that it is a subsequence of the target string. This approach is efficient as it avoids nested loops and has a linear time complexity.

